==English==
===Noun===
'''supplement'''
# something [[added]], especially to make up for a [[deficiency]]
# an [[extension]] to a [[document]] or [[publication]] that [[add]]s [[information]], [[correct]]s [[error]]s or brings [[up to date]]
# an [[additional]] [[section]] of a [[newspaper]] [[devote]]d to a specific [[subject]]
# {{Geometry}} an [[angle]] that, when added to a given angle, makes 180°; a [[supplementary angle]].
# {{bodybuilding}}: A [[vitamin]], [[herbal]] [[extract]], or [[chemical]] compound included with a [[diet]] to enhance [[muscular]] development.

===Transitive verb===
'''to supplement'''
# to [[provide]] or [[make]] a supplement to something
